# Branch Before Implementation

Never start writing code on the current branch. A dedicated branch must exist before any implementation begins.

## Decision Flow

### 1. User provided a Linear task link or ID

Extract the task identifier (e.g. `DUO-42`) and title, then **create the branch automatically** following the naming convention:

```
feat/<DUO-42>/<short-description>
fix/<DUO-42>/<short-description>
chore/<DUO-42>/<short-description>
```

Pick the prefix (`feat`, `fix`, `chore`) based on the task type. The `<short-description>` **must always be in English**, using kebab-case — even if the task title is in Portuguese, translate it.

```
# ❌ BAD
feat/DUO-42/secao-sobre-nos

# ✅ GOOD
feat/DUO-42/about-section
```

### 2. No Linear task context

Ask the user for the Linear task link before proceeding:

> "Qual é o link ou ID da task no Linear para essa implementação?"

### 3. Uncertain whether a new branch is needed

If already on a feature branch or unsure whether the work belongs on a new branch, ask:

> "Quer que eu crie uma nova branch para essa implementação?"

## Rules

- **Check `git branch --show-current`** at the start — if on `main` or `master`, a new branch is mandatory.
- **Never commit implementation work directly to `main`/`master`.**
- After creating the branch, confirm to the user before writing any code.
